      "content": "It's pretty standard procedure. Basically, instead of maintaining a separate, smaller model just for medical stuff, we take your specialized weights and integrate them into a much bigger, more capable architecture. This way, the general model gets your diagnostic accuracy, and we save on server costs by not running a dedicated instance. It's just an upgrade to be more efficient.",
